	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=20240><span id=Scholar>Arakonn</span></a><br><b><span id=Scholar>Scholar</span></b><br><span id=notbold>20 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent [3.00]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>Well, this matter is so complex that I started a website about the Paladin class, though you might find it not too usefull, as it is in German.<br><br>Generally, the paladin class has some severe drawbacks, which does not make it very popular in groups at higher levels. You have to be dedicated and have a lot of endurance to make it up towards legendary status, or whatever goals you set for yourself.<br><br>Concerning race choose the one you like. Some races have higher wisdom, which makes your casting capabilities better, other have higher combat stats (STR, AGI), which improves your combat performance. Decide on personal attitude, not on the best stats.<br><br>Best way to start is to look up a guide on one of the bigger sites (check here at Allakhazam under "Classes") and have a look at it. You will also need a list of the spells, as a description of their effects cannot be found ingame.<br><br>And, at last, choose this class because you love to be one, not because you want to play the best and coolest class in EQ - because that is a bit far from the truth.<br><br></p>&nbsp;<br>Arakonn Dragonblade<br>Grandmaster<br>Nova Militia Templaris<br>www.nova-militia.com<br></td></td></tr>
